question: (Sarah of the Clue Crew shows a bunch of jar-preserved specimens.)  Butterflies, centipedes, scorpions, spiders, crabs, lobsters--these & millions of other creepy crawlers belong to this phylum that makes up more than 80% of all animal species, from the Greek for "joint foot"
